SETUP GUIDE - ZOMBI TOOLS v1.0
Requirements
System Requirements

OS: Windows 10 (Build 19041+) or Windows 11
Python: Version 3.7 or higher
RAM: 2GB minimum
Admin: Administrator access required


Step 1: Install Python
Download Python

Go to https://www.python.org/downloads/
Click the yellow "Download Python 3.x.x" button
Download the Windows installer (64-bit)

Install Python

Double-click the downloaded python-3.x.x-amd64.exe file
IMPORTANT: Check the box "Add Python to PATH" before clicking Install
Click "Install Now"
Wait for installation to complete

Verify Python Installation

Open Command Prompt (Windows key + R, type cmd, press Enter)
Type: python --version
You should see: Python 3.x.x

If you see the version number, Python is installed correctly ✓

Step 2: Download ZOMBI TOOLS
Option 1: Download from GitHub Releases (Easiest)

Go to https://github.com/NYC0DEV/ZOMBI-TOOLS/releases
Download Zombi_Tools_V1_0.py
Save to your Desktop or Documents folder

Option 2: Download from GitHub Code

Go to https://github.com/NYC0DEV/ZOMBI-TOOLS
Click green "Code" button
Select "Download ZIP"
Extract the ZIP file
Find Zombi_Tools_V1_0.py


Step 3: Run ZOMBI TOOLS
Method 1: Double-Click (Easiest)

Find Zombi_Tools_V1_0.py on your computer
Double-click the file
Click "Yes" when Windows asks for admin permission
The application starts automatically
Dependencies auto-install on first run

Method 2: Command Prompt

Open Command Prompt (Windows key + R, type cmd, press Enter)
Navigate to the file location:

   cd Desktop
(Or: cd Downloads or cd Documents)

Run the application:

   python Zombi_Tools_V1_0.py

Click "Yes" when Windows asks for admin permission
The application starts


First Run
On first run, the application will:

Install required dependencies automatically
Create configuration files (settings.txt, keypad_resume.txt, keys.txt)
Show a message: "✓ All dependencies ready"
Open the ZOMBI TOOLS window

This is normal - just wait for the window to open.

Hotkeys
KeyFunctionF1Close overlay / Stop auto-clickerF3Toggle timerF4Settings menuCtrl+ZUndo circleCtrl+YRedo circle

Troubleshooting
"Python is not recognized"

Reinstall Python and CHECK "Add Python to PATH"
Close Command Prompt and open a new one after installing

Missing Dependencies Error

These auto-install on first run
If not, run in Command Prompt to see error messages

Admin Permission Error

Right-click the file → "Run as administrator"

File Permission Denied

Right-click file → Properties → Click "Unblock" → Click OK

"Game not found"

Make sure ZombiU is running
The app auto-detects the game


